Institutions.RCProfile: 1,232-acre campus in Berkeley (population: 116,768); 10 miles from San Francisco. Served by bus and train; major airports serve San Francisco and Oakland. School operates transportation to three nearby universities. Public transportation serves campus.

Institutions.Name: Boston University
Institutions.RCProfile: Urban campus in Boston (population: 645,966), plus 135 acres along the Charles River; medical center campus in downtown Boston. Served by air, bus, and train. Public transportation serves campus.
BulletPoints: BU is a private university with 300+ academic programs in 10 undergraduate schools and colleges
100% need met for admitted first-year students who are US citizens or permanent residents
Students are from 118+ countries and all 50 states, and 24% of first-year students are international
Residential community in the heart of Boston offering four years of guaranteed on-campus housing
Ranked #10 for employability in the US with 93% of students employed within 6 months of graduation

ContentItem.Title: Welcome to Boston University!
ContentItem.Description: Check out the official Boston University YouTube channel, a space for storytellers across campus to share what it's like to B-U. From scoring that game-winning goal, capturing a day-in-the-life on Commonwealth Avenue, uncovering a new research innovation, or connecting with those who make our campus feel like home, we're capturing it all, one video at a time.

Institutions.Name: University of Southern California
Institutions.RCProfile: 229-acre urban campus in Los Angeles (population: 3,844,307). Served by air, bus, and train. Public transportation serves campus.

Institutions.Name: University of California (Davis)
Institutions.RCProfile: 5,300-acre campus in Davis (population: 66,205), 15 miles from Sacramento. Served by bus and train; small airport on campus; major airport serves Sacramento. School operates transportation to Sacramento Medical Center. Public transportation serves campus.

Institutions.Name: Yale University
Institutions.RCProfile: 342-acre, urban campus in New Haven (population: 130,660), 42 miles from Hartford. Served by air, bus, and train; airports are in Hartford and New York City area. School operates transportation around campus and to some off-campus locations.

Institutions.Name: Brown University
Institutions.RCProfile: 146-acre campus in Providence (population: 177,994), 55 miles from Boston. Served by bus and train; major airport serves Boston; smaller airport serves Warwick (10 miles). School operates transportation around campus. Public transportation serves campus.

BulletPoints: Among the top 5 universities in the nation for social mobility
The closest University of California campus to Silicon Valley

In a world of beavers, bears, and bobcats, UCSC is home to the mighty Banana Slug mascot

ContentItem.Title: Why UC Santa Cruz?
ContentItem.Description: UC Santa Cruz welcomes the best and brightest students from around the world. Our campus is ranked a top 35 public university, an AAU research university, and the second best university in the country for social mobilityall in one of the most visually spectacular settings in higher education.

Institutions.RCProfile: 36-acre campus in New York City (population: 8,405,837). School operates transportation to Medical Center Campus and Lamont-Doherty Campus.
